# Interview Follow-up Questions

### Q1

Why Sliding Window?

Because the substring is continuous and we want an optimal solution.

---

### Q2

Why HashMap?

To maintain the frequency of characters inside the current window.

---

### Q3

Why While Loop?

Because a single removal may not eliminate all duplicates.

---

### Q4

Why O(n) instead of O(n²)?

Each pointer only moves forward.

Each character enters and leaves the window at most once.

---

### Q5

What invariant do you maintain?

The current window always contains unique characters.

---

# Interview Vocabulary

Instead of:

> "I move i."

Say:

> "I shrink the window from the left."

---

Instead of:

> "I add a character."

Say:

> "I expand the window by including the current character."

---

Instead of:

> "I remove a character."

Say:

> "I decrement the frequency of the leftmost character and move the left pointer."

